The paper discusses the construction of text indexes, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and is relevant to several subfields. The use of suffix arrays is particularly relevant to data compression, data mining, and Bioinformatics, which are covered by cs.DS, cs.IR, and cs.DB, respectively. The paper also mentions the use of advanced computational models such as external memory and distributed computing, which are covered by cs.CC and cs.DC, respectively. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely to be relevant to this paper.
